Install apps in Raspberry Pi using domestic mirror in China
<>bash
ping -c 4 pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn 

*Update APT source to a Mirror*
<>Bash
sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list
Replace the content with the 清华大学 (Tsinghua) mirror 
deb http://tsinghua.edu.cn bookworm main
Update the package list:
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

Install matplotlib from inside China
<>bash
python3 -m pip install matplotlib -i https://pypi.tuna.tsinghua.edu.cn/simple --break-system-packages
Verify installation
<>Python
import matplotlib
print (‘ok’)
Verify installation
<>Python
import cv2
print(cv2.__version__)

Upgrade pip: Ensure your pip is up-to-date to avoid issues
<>Bash
python -m pip install --upgrade pip -i https://tsinghua.edu.cn

#Ensure Prerequisites are Installed 
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3-full

#Creating Virtual Environment
<>Bash
python3 -m venv myenv

#Activate environment
<>Bash
source myenv/bin/activate

#Install OpenCV from Virtual Environment
<>Bash
pip3 install opencv-contrib-python -i https://tsinghua.edu.cn

